Markland’s conjecture εἴληφεν ἄν involves not only a solecism, but a wrong sense. For ‘⁴ he would have received the money ’' (εἰλήφει ἂν) implies ‘⁸ but he has not received the money. ’⁹ But Demosthenes states broadly that Aeschines has received it.
